  "local_port": 37242,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I have to pay the installments once I bought something through krazybee?",
  "response": "Paying installments for purchases made through KrazyBee is straightforward. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide to help you manage your installment payments:\n\n### **1. Log into Your KrazyBee Account**\n- **Mobile App:** Open the KrazyBee app on your smartphone and sign in with your credentials.\n- **Website:** Visit the KrazyBee website and log in using your username and password.\n\n### **2. Navigate to Your Orders**\n- Once logged in, go to the **\"My Orders\"** or **\"Purchases\"** section. This is typically found in the main menu or under your account/profile section.\n\n### **3. Select the Relevant Purchase**\n- Locate the item you purchased on an installment plan.\n- Click on the order to view detailed information about your payment schedule.\n\n### **4. Review Your Installment Plan**\n- **Payment Schedule:** Check the dates and amounts for each installment.\n- **Total Amount:** Ensure you know the total amount financed and any applicable interest or fees.\n\n### **5. Choose Your Payment Method**\nKrazyBee usually offers multiple payment options for installments:\n- **Credit/Debit Card:** Add or select a saved card to set up recurring payments.\n- **Bank Transfer:** Link your bank account for direct debit setups.\n- **UPI:** Use Unified Payments Interface (if available) for quick transfers.\n- **Net Banking:** Utilize online banking facilities provided by your bank.\n\n### **6. Set Up Automatic Payments (Recommended)**\n- **Enable Auto-Debit:** To avoid missing payments, set up automatic deductions on your preferred payment method.\n- **Authorization:** You may need to authorize KrazyBee to debit your account automatically. Follow the on-screen instructions to complete this setup.\n\n### **7. Manual Payment Option**\n- If you prefer, you can choose to make payments manually each month:\n  - **Payment Due Reminders:** Enable notifications to remind you of upcoming payments.\n  - **Make a Payment:** On the due date, go to the payment section and complete the payment using your chosen method.\n\n### **8. Confirm and Save Your Payment Settings**\n- After selecting your preferred payment method and setting up automatic or manual payments, confirm the details.\n- Save the settings to ensure your payments are processed as scheduled.\n\n### **9. Monitor Your Payments**\n- **Regular Checks:** Regularly check your KrazyBee account to ensure payments are being deducted correctly.\n- **Receipts:** Keep an eye out for payment confirmations via email or within the app.\n\n### **10. Contact Customer Support if Needed**\n- If you encounter any issues or have questions about your installment plan, reach out to KrazyBee\u2019s customer support:\n  - **In-App Support:** Use the chat feature within the app.\n  - **Email:** Send a detailed query to their support email address.\n  - **Phone:** Call their customer service hotline for immediate assistance.\n\n### **Additional Tips**\n- **Maintain Sufficient Funds:** Ensure your chosen payment method has sufficient funds to cover each installment to avoid late fees or service interruptions.\n- **Update Payment Information:** If you change your bank account or card details, update them promptly in your KrazyBee account to ensure seamless payments.\n- **Review Terms:** Familiarize yourself with KrazyBee\u2019s installment terms and conditions, including any interest rates or additional fees.\n\nBy following these steps, you can efficiently manage and pay your installments for purchases made through KrazyBee. Always stay informed about your payment schedule and keep track of your financial commitments to maintain a good credit standing.\n\nIf you need more specific assistance, visiting KrazyBee\u2019s official website or contacting their customer support team directly is recommended.",
